   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Galaxy chemicals</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(i) Setting up environment friendly world class facilities compliant with International Regulatory Standards.   (ii) Employment Generation: The original project is expected to create nearly 110 jobs (including direct and indirect employment) with an additional 10 from the expansion.  Additional training opportunities for about 30 local engineers.   (iii) IFC&apos;&apos;s investment in the Company will have a significant number of direct and indirect development benefits such as linkages with local suppliers, upgrade of existing infrastructure, indirect employment creation through auxiliary businesses in the region.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed Project is an expansion of a greenfield plant in Egypt producing chemicals, primarily for export to large, international companies that manufacture home &amp; personal care products in MENA, Europe &amp; the Americas.  A majority of Galaxy Egypts sales will go to multinationals, many of which are currently supplied from the Sponsors existing operations in India.</narrative>
  </description>
